  "text": "Folin-Ciocalteu's method was used in determining the concentrations of total phenols [CITATION_1] . The preparation of samples was performed in triplicate and the mean value of absorbance was calculated. Gallic acid was used as a standard for calibration of standard curve. The linear equation of standard curve (y = 0.008x + 0.0077, R2 = 0.998) was used in calculating the total phenolic content. Finally, the total phenolic content was shown by form -milligram of gallic acid equivalent per gram of extract (mg of GAE/g of extract).",
